01:19:16,748 --> 01:19:19,810
Report on snow day, school cancellation protocols.

897
01:19:22,570 --> 01:19:31,236
So, the reason this is on your agenda is every year I get asked around this time, how do we decide when school closes and what can we do about it?

898
01:19:32,137 --> 01:19:34,699
Now, the main message is this.

899
01:19:35,860 --> 01:19:49,130
You should start planning now as a parent about a situation that might occur and who will help to cover your youngsters if you have to go to work, who's going to stay at home, what neighbors can work with you,

900
01:19:50,060 --> 01:19:51,520
What situations can occur?

901
01:19:51,540 --> 01:19:57,421
Can you talk to your employers, maybe coming in a little bit later on certain days to get things under control?

902
01:19:57,901 --> 01:19:59,742
You can't wait till the day it happens.

903
01:20:00,002 --> 01:20:01,262
You've got to start thinking about it.

904
01:20:01,822 --> 01:20:08,903
And oftentimes, we don't get a final call until later because we don't know if the storm is going to hit.

905
01:20:09,643 --> 01:20:13,124
You know, meteorologists do their job, but they can't be sure.

906
01:20:13,924 --> 01:20:18,345
Sometimes the storm veers off at the last second, and sometimes it veers in at the last second.

907
01:20:19,000 --> 01:20:20,041
And we need to be careful.

908
01:20:20,121 --> 01:20:28,490
And sometimes the storm doesn't seem like it's coming to us at the beginning of school, but it's going to hit at 10 o'clock in the morning and getting young people home is its own problem.

909
01:20:29,231 --> 01:20:34,277
The other thing that we have to deal with is the fact that some youngsters have no one at home on a regular basis.

910
01:20:35,057 --> 01:20:39,602
And getting them to school means they might need a hot meal, they have some supervision.

911
01:20:40,874 --> 01:20:44,258
There's some other things going on that we want to provide.

912
01:20:44,919 --> 01:20:50,686
On the other hand, if you really feel uptight, you really feel like maybe your child shouldn't be out, it's your option to keep them home.

913
01:20:51,948 --> 01:20:55,853
Missing a day is not going to change the world as long as you're diligent about following up on the work.

914
01:20:57,179 --> 01:20:58,380
We've got to understand these things.

915
01:20:58,440 --> 01:20:59,900
Now it takes a lot to figure this out.

916
01:20:59,920 --> 01:21:11,265
We talk to the DPW, we talk to the police department, we talk to the fire department, we talk to our own custodial crews, we talk to the contractors who plow our schools, we talk to neighbors.

917
01:21:11,825 --> 01:21:12,646
What are they doing?

918
01:21:12,706 --> 01:21:13,546
How are they doing it?

919
01:21:14,426 --> 01:21:16,127
And some places are more challenging than others.

920
01:21:16,567 --> 01:21:22,410
If you live in the narrow streets of Everett and Malden, it's a lot tougher to plow those streets than it is maybe in Medford.

921
01:21:23,443 --> 01:21:32,507
It's a lot tougher to do certain things and they have to make decisions a little bit earlier because they can't get their crews out as fast as our crews get out.

922
01:21:34,528 --> 01:21:35,389
We want to provide.

923
01:21:36,389 --> 01:21:37,249
intelligent days.

924
01:21:37,529 --> 01:21:40,190
We also have to think about the days if teachers can't get there.

925
01:21:40,690 --> 01:21:47,853
So school is open and the faculty can't make it in because they no longer all live in Medford or one community over.

926
01:21:48,413 --> 01:21:50,133
People live in wider areas.

927
01:21:50,753 --> 01:21:55,495
So to have a day where the faculty is missing doesn't give us a quality education day.

928
01:21:56,275 --> 01:21:58,696
We started earlier this year, so that should help.

929
01:21:59,657 --> 01:22:02,099
In terms of days, but you never know.

930
01:22:02,880 --> 01:22:04,702
We've had years where there's been no school days.

931
01:22:05,102 --> 01:22:07,904
We've had years when a couple of years ago there were seven or eight school days.

932
01:22:08,565 --> 01:22:09,486
And last year there were three.

933
01:22:10,166 --> 01:22:11,107
So it's hard to know.

934
01:22:11,227 --> 01:22:14,150
And one year we shut down schools when the buildings were too cold.

935
01:22:15,331 --> 01:22:17,453
And it wasn't a question of snow, it just was too cold.

936
01:22:18,294 --> 01:22:19,355
So there's a lot of reasons.

937
01:22:20,215 --> 01:22:21,717
And we try to be up front.

938
01:22:21,737 --> 01:22:25,320
There's always somebody who tells me we shouldn't have done it, and there's somebody who always tells me we should have done it.

939
01:22:26,063 --> 01:22:26,723
I mean, I guarantee you.

940
01:22:26,743 --> 01:22:28,604
